
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates the usage of the [strings.replace] slot to replace occurrences of a specified substring within a source string. The code retrieves the source string from [.arguments/*/source], the substring to be replaced from [.arguments/*/what], and the replacement string from [.arguments/*/with], effectively substituting all occurrences of the specified substring in the source string with the new value.
strings.replace:x:@.arguments/*/source
   get-value:x:@.arguments/*/what
   get-value:x:@.arguments/*/with
